tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c (6.1%), suggesting impaired glucose tolerance or early diabetes. Creatinine is slightly elevated, indicating possible mild renal impairment. Chloride is marginally high but likely not clinically significant. Other parameters, including blood counts, electrolytes, and metabolic markers, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and monitoring of glycemic control and renal function.
